dct_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Stryj, sheet U-18. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dct_description_sm: AMS 1. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Stryj, Poland. Polyconic projection. Danube zone grid. Relief shown by 20 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, 1931-35. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence information. Map states location as Poland though the map actually depicts Ukraine.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
